xnix: a small kernel for play
Written by Aaron Blakely <aaron@ephasic.org>

IRC: irc.alphachat.net #ephasic

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Need an i586 cross compiler?
Run mkcrosscompiler.sh in etc/tools :)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Building:

KVM/QUEMU support is dodgy.  I recommend using bochs, or actual hardware.

You'll need to make an initrd, to do so compile etc/mkinitrd/mkinitrd.c and run it, then coppy the initrd.img file to kernel/

To make a floppy image just use: make floppy
To make run in bochs: make bochs

	
